content:
Hello <@&897901485713666068>! 

Lately there have been a massive amount of scammers roaming around Discord, so i'd like to give a warning to everyone about it. We get up to 1-3 of these attacks weekly and it happens when someone clicks a link (often a disguised link), your account is then hacked and your account does the same in the Discord servers you are in.

We ask you to use extreme caution when clicking a link, not only for yourself but for others sake as well. I will tell you that there is no such thing as free money, easy access to money or some random dude on the internet that gives you a gift, so if there is someone who tells you that they can double your money with crypto or giving you a free Steam gift etc - it's most likely a lie, and NEVER EVER click the links they are linking, do not fall for the temptation of clicking OnlyFans links or Discord invite links either (unless the Discord invite link is allowed by Devs or Server Staff).

You bear full responsibility for your own Discord account, should your account start spamming then we will have to ban it from the server in order to quickly stop the spread. If you ever see such a scam attempt, quickly type <@&899682367273316442> and someone with the ability to ban will do so as soon as they notice. Again, do not click links, especially if they have no embed attached to it like a news article or YouTube link would.

On a general level, i would advice you to have what we call cyber hygiene, this includes running full virus scans daily, changing your passwords once per month (strong ones recommended - example: #CoTt0nC@nd1LitE) and using multi-factor authentication.

Thank you for taking the time to read!

content:
Hi everyone, 
@everyone 

I wanted to let you know that we are currently working on fixing everything that has been reported.

We've been trying to address all the issues over the past few days, but as we squash bugs, more seem to pop up from another place.

Therefore, we have decided to delay any new features for the next few weeks in favor of bug fixing.

I understand that the economy integration is not working well at the moment - the data seems strange and the values are unrealistic. This has been the primary reason for the delays so far.

The economy system is brand new and needs more time in the oven, as well as testing by all of you.

I know some of you may feel disappointed, and for that, we apologize. But rest assured, those bugs will be fixed as soon as possible.

**For those who are waiting for the game to be more playable, please wait a bit longer.**

The first hotfix will be released soon (a matter of days).

❤️💪

Hey @everyone! UPDATE 0.85 is live on steam!

We got as far as we could on revamping military and economy. But there is certainly some weird stuff going on!

Remember to post feedback good and bad! We will be delivering a hotfix to some known issues soon! (GDP/inflation, strategic unit cards not grouping properly etc.)

But any feedback on the new UI would especially help as we make tweaks in the first hot fix!

Also it’s now available on Mac!

Change log tomorrow.

HAPPY HUNTING

**Update 0.85 Delayed to Monday evening (EST US time)**
Hello everyone, thanks for your patience thus far BUT I have to be the bearer of bad news, and I have decided to delay the patch to Monday evening.

This patch is massive, pretty much redoing the Economy and much of Warfare
(Like ya know the title of the game).
There's a brand new UI as well as visual improvements through out.

While I was redoing the interactions for naval and land units I came across a design flaw that either I fix now or it will haunt us for the entirety of the development cycle. After this patch comes out I will be listening careful for feedback, the system is much easier to alter now!

We are also changing our standards for what can be shipped (acceptable bugs and what not). So we in the future will be more careful about what dates we put out there, this happened because of bad communication between Lotus and I.

Apologies from both of us.

**I WANT YOU FIGHTING WARS NOT BUGS.**

The time has arrived!!! (7.35 hours from now !)

We are both nervous and excited to hear everyone's responses. 
We also want to be completely honest and open with you regarding the state of the game, so we're sharing an open letter with you.

We're not here just to take your money and run away; we're here to make this the best geopolitical game that has ever been released so far. And that's not an easy task for an indie studio with only four employees.

So, the next period will be dedicated to early access where we will fix EVERYTHING, make things more immersive, and listen to feedbacks.

I want to say loud and clear: DON'T BUY THE GAME if you're not willing to understand that you're jumping into an early access game. Bad reviews can undermine our efforts to reach a point where we are all satisfied and happy with the game.

Hello <@&897901485713666068>!

I hope this message finds you well. Today, I want to address a serious issue that has come to my attention. It has been observed that there have been conversations within our server that are not only inappropriate but deeply concerning. Specifically, there have been instances of hateful speech directed towards Jews and Muslims.

Let me be crystal clear: our server is a place for everyone to feel safe, respected, and valued, regardless of their religion, race, ethnicity, or background. Hate speech, derogatory comments, and especially any calls for violence or genocide against any group are absolutely unacceptable and will not be tolerated under any circumstances.

We all come from diverse backgrounds and hold different beliefs, which is a strength that enriches our community. However, respect and empathy towards others are non-negotiable. Here, we stand firmly against hate and prejudice.

**Effective immediately:**

**Zero-Tolerance Policy: Any member found engaging in hate speech or promoting violence will face immediate and permanent removal from this server.**

**Review and Moderation: Our moderation team will increase vigilance in monitoring conversations. We encourage members to report any concerning behavior or content to the moderators.**

We must all take responsibility for the environment we create and maintain online. Let's work together to ensure our server remains a welcoming and safe space for everyone. If you have questions or concerns, feel free to reach out to the moderation team.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation!

Hey <@&897901485713666068>! Just so people know, if you have not received a rejection answer from the Application Bot, it means your application is among those that are being considered so there is no need to create a new application. If your application was denied it is because:

- Some of the applications had too little info.
- Some did not write down the hours in their top 3 played games.
- Some had too few hours played in the Grand Strategy genre.
- Some had insufficient PC specs.

You are free to make a new application if you have been denied, but you must put in the correct info, that means all of your PC specs (not just a couple of them, all of them) and the amount of hours you have played in your top 3 played games.

We are sorry for the inconvenience to those that do not meet the minimum requirement, we need to prioritize those that have most hours together with best PC specs because Okron Studio cannot afford to give away hundreds of keys. <@712473098540023809> will go through the applications that wasn't denied before the beta phase starts.

Thanks and sorry again to those that were rejected!

Greetings all <@&897901485713666068> || @everyone || ! How’s everyone doing today? I hope all is well <:awesome:894438664657047623>!

The time has come... Yes... This is possibly one of the most awaited announcements all of you have been waiting for!.. It’s none other than,** Scenarios Competition**! YES, you read it right, Citizens!


As many of you know, we already have a <#901771019671441469>channel where we have been given a lot of incredible suggestions by you all; quite enticing if you ask me. This made us think, why not reward people for such fantastic ideas. So we thought, why not run a competition where all of you amazing Citizens can participate and vote on the three best scenarios … And YES, there will be prizes. <:nodypeek:851791311869706271> 

The rules of this competition are pretty simple. You’re allowed to post **one scenario** only in <#1082761933809270784> (currently locked). The competition submissions will be open for** 61 days**, and after that, the channel will be locked and made public to all non-participants. Citizens can vote anytime whenever they feel they wish to vote on the best scenario, and the 3 Scenarios with the most votes will be our winners! We really don’t have any specific window for the voting, which means, you’ll be able to vote as long as submissions are open, which is till May 16th, 2023.

Below are the emojis you can use for voting:-👍for upvote and 👎for the downvote.

Please do note that we have necessary **spam detectors** and an **alt accounts identifier** installed in the server, which would restrict such users in the first place; however, If we’re to find that anyone is trying to win by buying votes or faking the votes using their alt account, they will be forfeited from this competition and possibly from future competitions If their behavior doesn’t improve. They might lose all the perks they have in the channel, and, If they’re part of the Beta or Alpha tester, such privileges will be revoked at that very instance. 

The competition will begin **on March 13th**, and SUBMISSION WILL BE OPEN **TILL May 16th**.


**Please note, the following are the topics or subjects you should avoid at all costs when it comes to scenarios submission: -**

Topics include **discrimination against race, creed, gender, religion, any sort of transphobic comments or anything which hurts anyone’s sentiments or beliefs**. 


Furthermore, **any sort of sci-fi scenario, such as an Alien Invasion** or anything which is in regard as** sci-fi**, is prohibited. 

Following is the structure you’ll be submitting your scenarios ➖

E.g., **Title**:- COLD WAR 
**Explanation**: - Explain this scenario to us with some examples. If you have, it’s optional to give an example, but it will help the audience better!

If you have any discrepancies about this or any doubts, please reach out <@100114514191597568>  or <@&1075074946461601792> for the same, and they will get back to you!

Good luck, everyone! 

Kind regards
Nody,
Community Manager.

Hello @everyone and <@&897901485713666068> 

In the past week we though a lot about the upcoming beta and we feel that we are not ready yet for a beta unfortunately.
The game currently been tested by our dedicated alpha testers and by our QA testers and they all can confirm that we still need more time to reach Beta.

As I said from day one, I won’t release an unfinished game no matter what will happens ! Beta means people need to pay for the game and we all feel that currently it will be inappropriate to charge you guys for that state of the game. 

I’m sorry to disappoint many of you but I’m promise that I’m disappointing everyone now so on release you all be satisfied ! 

As a gamer myself there are too many games out here that charging full price for half working game - and this is exactly what Okron Studio wants to change ! We want every game that we will release to be fully immersive and functional for that we gathered a community of players that will help determine our games state - so the release decision won’t be make by finance restrictions or profits it will be make by actual gamers who agree that our games can be release.

We hoping to release a closed Beta around April - and Open Beta (Early Access on Steam) around July

I’m sorry again for the disappointment believe me that there is nothing on earth I want more than releasing the game but not like that - we need more patience from you. 
 
Thank you for you dedication and hype you feeling towards the game ! We promise to do the best we can to deliver the best geopolitical experience you can think of !

Reminder that there is a contest that are ongoing which can give you a free copy and/or beta access. Alpha access is now closed!

**The Invite Competition:**
The members who invite the most people will win this competition, the competition will last until the beta version of World Warfare & Economics is released! The ones who are on 1st to 3rd place when the beta is released will come out on top of the competition and gain access to beta immediately once it's released! 4th to 10th place will be rewarded two weeks after release of the beta (beta release is planned for February 2023). 

• 1st place - Free copy + beta participating;
• 2nd place - Free copy + beta participating;
• 3rd place - Free copy + beta participating;
• 4th-10th place - Free copy + beta participating (announced two weeks after beta release).

Each member can generate only one valid invitation link, make sure it's a permanent link to compete - if you have two different invitation links, know that only one link will be valid and we will choose the one you have most invites on. This is not a competition that requires you to bring in a certain amount of people, the ones who has the most invited members when this competition is over, wins. As you can see there are not only one winner but up to 10 people will be rewarded in this competition!

How you can encourage people to join:
- Talk about the game and this community in your social medias and other communities that could be interested in this game and this community.
- Show your interests about the game or the community.
- Explain the development process (single developer with an open community for feedback and ideas).
- Talk about the features of the game, show screenshots or videos/trailers.
- Ask people with high amount of followers/subscribers to post something regarding World Warfare & Economics, if you know any that could be interested in such games.

If found to be inviting completely new members to the discord server all the time, it will be viewed as an attempt to be using alt accounts. We can see the age of accounts that join the server so please don't do this, we would also prefer if you invited people who is likely to stay and play the game and talk. If you have lost your permanent invitation link, you can DM a mod or an admin so they can find your link. @everyone

@everyone  Hi all !

I'm glad to see all the new faces around here, welcome 🙂

So as you can all know I will start my own studio very soon and that's very good news for World Warfare & Economics, I want to share with you the new features that the game will include..

1. Multiplayer mod with up to 32 players will be added on release date
2. WW2 (including cold war era) DLC will be published along with the base game on release date (You will be able to start from year 1932 up to infinity, all military units from that era including cold war era and scenarios)
3. Further mods: WW1 + Futuristic era (aliens invasions and more cool stuff)
4. Every year all players will get free major update with updated data and features
5. Full modding support with steam workshop support + Include in house modding tool (including scripting)
6. Official trailer should be released by the end of May
7. Streaming videos will start to take place on the Steam page from July 2022
8. DLCs will be dedicated to era's and new military units and scenarios - all the mechanics of the game will be included in the base game !
9. New photos will be upload in the next few days

**Limited Early access (alpha) will be available on November 2022 for Patreon and localization teams only - no competitors winners**
**Please keep writing your ideas some of them are already implemented into the game !**
